  "ID": "a0688719-1749-4079-a65b-212c52c3a74a",
  "Title": "指令舱驾驶员认证飞行",
  "Description": "指令舱驾驶员认证飞行将测试你所学到的关于阿波罗指令舱操作的知识。它将从卡纳维拉尔角发射开始，上升进入轨道，在那里你将绕地球轨道飞行，然后执行再入。",
  "BriefingText": "指挥舱驾驶员认证飞行\r\n\r\nWelcome to the Apollo Command Module Pilot Certification Flight. Successful completion of this mission will result in the awarding of the Command Module Pilot Certificate.\r\n\r\nThis is a solo flight, designed to test your ability to perform as an Apollo Command Module pilot. You’ll be responsible for all mission-critical decisions, and the outcome will depend on how you handle each phase of the flight.\r\n\r\nMISSION OBJECTIVES\r\n- Launch and achieve Earth orbit.\r\n- Complete post-insertion checklist operations.\r\n- Perform two (2) orbital burns to raise perigee/apogee.\r\n- Execute deorbit burn, controlled reentry, and splashdown.\r\n\r\nMISSION TIMELINE\r\nThe following timeline provides a suggested sequence of events. You are free to divert from this plan as needed to complete the mission.\r\nT+00:00:00 - Launch\r\nT+00:11:30 - Orbit insertion, begin post-insertion checklist\r\nT+01:20:00 - Separate from the LV (CSM/LV SEP)\r\nT+01:30:00 - Plan first orbital burn: Apogee raise to 220 nmi\r\nT+02:00:00 - Ignition: First orbital burn\r\nT+02:05:00 - Plan second orbital burn: Perigee raise to 220 nmi\r\nT+02:45:00 - Ignition: Second orbital burn\r\nT+06:00:00 - Deorbit burn (initiate reentry trajectory)\r\nT+06:35:00 - Atmospheric interface\r\nT+06:40:00 - Main parachute deploy\r\nT+06:50:00 - Splashdown and recovery\r\n\r\nMISSION GUIDE\r\n1) Complete the PRE-LAUNCH: LAUNCH PREPARATIONS checklist\r\n2) Complete the ascent\r\n3) Complete the insertion checks\r\n4) Complete the CSM/LV SEP (NO T&D) checks\r\n5) Plan a burn at Perigee to rise Ap to 220 nmi alt\r\n   Estimated parameters: phase=0, dV ~200 ft/s\r\n6) Execute the burn using P30, P52 opt 1, and P40\r\n7) Plan and execute a burn to circularize the orbit to 220 nmi\r\n   Estimated parameters: phase=180, dV ~200 ft/s\r\n8) Deorbit, Entry and Landing\r\n\r\nDeorbit, Entry and Landing steps:\r\nI)   Follow the EARTH ENTRY: EARTH ORBIT ENTRY VEHICLE to plan a deorbit burn with an entry angle of 1.5 degrees (do not use 2 degrees in the exam to get a bit more time for procedures), and prepare for entry.\r\n\r\nII)  Follow the EARTH ENTRY: SPS DEORBIT & ENTRY to complete the deorbit burn and atmospheric entry.\r\n\r\nIII) Follow the EARTH ENTRY: EARTH LANDING for a safe landing\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGood luck!",
